  "text": "The who category includes three themes relating to instructors and participants. The theme of instructor indicated two important aspects in relation to debriefing instructors (i.e., level of involvement and characteristics). [CITATION_1] found that approximately 85% of the total studies (n = 154 of 177) involved educators (i.e., instructors) in their debriefing practice. However, Table 3 shows that although a total of seven papers addressed the importance of instructor-led debriefing, their evaluation was based on the reviewers' reflections in most cases (n = 4). In addition, only one paper reported the participants' preference [CITATION_2] , while two addressed inconclusive effects.",
